title: QUALCOMM INCORPORATED
description:
QUALCOMM Incorporated is a leading multinational corporation headquartered in San Diego, California, known for its significant contributions to the telecommunications and semiconductor industries. The company is renowned for its development and commercialization of wireless telecommunications products and services, including semiconductors, telecommunications equipment, and digital wireless communications products. It operates through several segments, notably Qualcomm CDMA Technologies (QCT), Qualcomm Technology Licensing (QTL), and Qualcomm Strategic Initiatives (QSI), focusing on semiconductors, licensing, and strategic investments, respectively.

QUALCOMM is a key player in mobile and wireless technology, particularly in 3G, 4G, and next-generation wireless technologies, including 5G. The company derives its revenue from the sales of integrated circuit products, licensing of intellectual property, and providing development and other services. It is involved in the design and marketing of digital wireless telecommunications products and services, including semiconductors and software for mobile devices, automotive systems, and IoT products.

Financially, QUALCOMM is engaged in various activities such as tax management, stock repurchases, and earnings per share calculations. It is subject to income taxes in the United States and numerous foreign jurisdictions and participates in the IRS Compliance Assurance Process program. The company provides comprehensive financial statements and marketable securities information, including fair value measurements and management's discussion and analysis of financial condition and results of operations. It operates on a 52-53 week fiscal year ending on the last Sunday in September and reports financial results in accordance with GAAP.

QUALCOMM is also involved in various legal and regulatory proceedings, including disputes with ParkerVision and Arm Ltd. over patent and licensing issues, as well as antitrust and patent infringement issues. The company has been active in acquisitions, such as the acquisition of Veoneer, Inc.'s Arriver business, and Nuvia, Inc. It maintains various compensation and severance plans for its executives and directors and is involved in stock repurchase programs, dividend distributions, and employee benefit plans, including equity compensation and stock purchase plans.

Overall, QUALCOMM Incorporated is a global technology leader specializing in wireless connectivity, high-performance computing, and on-device AI, with a vast patent portfolio and a strong presence in the semiconductor industry.
